## File a bug

According to [the documentation](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/ef/core/modeling/entity-types?tabs=data-annotations#view-mapping):

> Mapping to a view will remove the default table mapping, but the entity type can also be mapped to a table explicitly. In this case the query mapping will be used for queries and **the table mapping will be used for updates.**

However, ExecuteUpdate does not respect this - it updates the view, not the table.

### Include your code

Instructions:

- Add Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Sqlite Nuget package
- Add Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Tools Nuget package
- Paste the code below into Program.cs in a console application
- Run `add-migration InitialCreate` followed by `update-database`
- Run the application

```C#
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;


using var db = new BloggingContext();

db.Database.ExecuteSql($"CREATE VIEW IF NOT EXISTS BlogsView AS SELECT * FROM Blogs");

var blog = new Blog { Url = "http://blogs.msdn.com/adonet" };
db.Add(blog);
db.SaveChanges();

blog.Url = "http://blogs.msdn.com/adonet2";
db.SaveChanges(); // Updates the Blogs table

// The following attempts to update the BlogsView view, not the Blogs table as expected.
// In SqLite, this throws an exception because views can not be updated.
// In Sql Server, it might succeed depending on the definition of the view
db.Blogs.ExecuteUpdate(properties => properties.SetProperty(b => b.Url, "http://blogs.msdn.com/adonet3"));


public class BloggingContext : DbContext
{
    public DbSet<Blog> Blogs { get; set; }

    public string DbPath { get; }

    public BloggingContext()
    {
        var folder = Environment.SpecialFolder.LocalApplicationData;
        var path = Environment.GetFolderPath(folder);
        DbPath = System.IO.Path.Join(path, "blogging.db");
    }

    protected override void OnConfiguring(DbContextOptionsBuilder options)
        => options.UseSqlite($"Data Source={DbPath}");

    protected override void OnModelCreating(ModelBuilder modelBuilder)
    {
        modelBuilder.Entity<Blog>()
            .ToTable("Blogs")
            .ToView("BlogsView");
    }
}

public class Blog
{
    public int BlogId { get; set; }
    public string Url { get; set; } = "";
}

```

### Include stack traces

When running this against SqLite, the following exception is generated:

```
